26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 9, Chapter 28, Subchapter 4, is amended
27 to add additional sections to read as follows:
28 9-28-417. Foster home training — Limitation on hours required.
29 (a) The Division of Children and Family Services shall not require a
30 foster home to obtain more than:
31 (1) Fifteen (15) hours of initial training to become an approved
32 foster home; or
33 (2) Six (6) hours of annual training to maintain the foster
34 home's status as an approved foster home.
35 (b) The division may reduce the hourly requirements under subsection
36 (a) of this section by rule.
